* Terrafrom builds an execution plan based on your terrafrom configurations changed
* Only modifies what is nessary to reach your desired state
* can Not only version control for configuration but also can see the historical state of infrastrucutre evolved over time
* Terraform first destroyed the existing instance and then created a new one in its place




Command list

    * command: terraform apply
      Notice that before perform the change, it is a nesscrary to make backup

    * command: terraform show
      show the newest infrastructure info after changing

    * command: terraform plan
       - show the changes what is required resource to be replaced
       - adjust your changes to possibly avoid destory/create/updates
   

